The paper is about a system for training Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) using pipeline parallelism, which is a technique for parallelizing computation across multiple machines. This suggests that the paper could belong to several different arXiv CS sub-categories, including Distributed and Parallel Computing (cs.DC), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and possibly others. However, given that the focus of the paper is on the efficiency and speed of DNN training, and that it proposes a new system for achieving these goals, it seems most likely that the paper belongs to the Distributed and Parallel Computing (cs.DC) category.
